---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const effectiveDate = '2026-05-02';
const email = 'nailsonsalon@gmail.com';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Nails On Salon"
  description="Privacy Policy for nailsonsalon.com — what we do not collect, third-party services that may process your data, and your California privacy rights."
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="bg-bg-tint py-2xl sm:py-3xl">
    <div class="px-5 sm:px-10 max-w-container-xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="font-display font-light text-display-mobile sm:text-display-desktop text-ink">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-body-large text-muted mt-md max-w-2xl">
        This website does not use cookies, contact forms, or analytics. Here is what that means in practice.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CONTENT -->
  <section class="bg-white py-2xl sm:py-3xl">
    <div class="px-5 sm:px-10 max-w-container-xl mx-auto">
      <article class="max-w-2xl space-y-xl text-body-base text-ink leading-relaxed">

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-h3-mobile sm:text-h3-desktop text-ink mb-md">
            1. Who We Are
          </h2>
          <p>
            Nails On Salon is operated by Tetiana Yaresko, a sole proprietor located at
            3030 Plaza Bonita Rd, Unit 1336, Suite 117, National City, CA 91950.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-h3-mobile sm:text-h3-desktop text-ink mb-md">
            2. Information We Do Not Collect
          </h2>
          <p>
            This website does not use cookies. It does not collect, store, or process any personal
            information directly. There are no contact forms or analytics on this website.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-h3-mobile sm:text-h3-desktop text-ink mb-md">
            3. Third-Party Services That May Process Your Data
          </h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-md">
            <li>
              <strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong> (hosting): our hosting provider may log standard server
              access data including IP addresses. See
              <a
                href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-ink underline decoration-brand decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-muted"
                aria-label="Cloudflare Privacy Policy (opens in new tab)"
              >Cloudflare's Privacy Policy</a>.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Instagram</strong>: clicking our Instagram link takes you to Instagram
              (Meta Platforms). Meta's data practices are governed by their
              <a
                href="https://privacycenter.instagram.com/policy"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-ink underline decoration-brand decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-muted"
                aria-label="Instagram Privacy Policy (opens in new tab)"
              >Privacy Policy</a>.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Google Maps</strong>: clicking the "View on Google Maps" link in our
              location section takes you to Google Maps. Google may collect standard request
              data such as your IP address, browser information, and referrer. See
              <a
                href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-ink underline decoration-brand decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-muted"
                aria-label="Google Privacy Policy (opens in new tab)"
              >Google's Privacy Policy</a>.
              We do not embed any Google content (no Maps iframe, no analytics, no fonts) — the
              data flow only occurs if you actively click the link.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-h3-mobile sm:text-h3-desktop text-ink mb-md">
            4. Instagram Booking
          </h2>
          <p>
            Booking is handled via Instagram Direct Message. Any information you share via DM is
            subject to Instagram's (Meta's) Privacy Policy, not ours.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-h3-mobile sm:text-h3-desktop text-ink mb-md">
            5. Your California Privacy Rights
          </h2>
          <p>
            As a California resident, you have rights under the CCPA/CPRA. Because we do not collect
            personal information through this website, there is no data to access, delete, or opt out of.
            For privacy questions:
            <a
              href={`mailto:${email}`}
              class="text-ink underline decoration-brand decoration-2 underline-offset-4 hover:text-muted"
            >{email}</a>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-h3-mobile sm:text-h3-desktop text-ink mb-md">
            6. Changes to This Policy
          </h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The "Effective Date" below indicates
            when this version was published. Continued use of this website after changes are posted
            constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="pt-lg border-t border-border">
          <p class="text-body-small text-muted">
            Effective Date: <time datetime={effectiveDate}>{effectiveDate}</time>
          </p>
        </div>

      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
